{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}The model fits fairly well, as there are more ones in the areas with higher fitted probabilities of occurrence.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}However, there certainly are some species that have high levels of occurence in sites that the model predicts they are rare...like this species or this one.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}Conversely, there are species that have low levels of occurence in sites that the model predicts that they should be relatively common...like this species or this one.\
{\listtext	\uc0\u8259 	}So we learn that there must be some other traits that we did not measure that can explain this pattern in the residuals.\
